      QueryHelper QueryHelper.subWhere​(java.lang.String subWhereClause)
      Validates the subWhereClause against the TildaSQL parser and if it passes, adds it to the current query object, in parenthesis as to be cohesive with the rest of the query.
      QueryHelper QueryHelper.subWhere​(QueryHelper.CaseClause clause)

      QueryHelper QueryHelper.within​(Type_DatetimePrimitive Col, Type_DatetimePrimitive ColStart, long durationCount, DurationUtil.IntervalEnum Type)
      If Duration is positive, implements the condition Col >= ColStart && Col < ColStart + interval specified.
      If Duration is negative, implements the condition Col > ColStart - interval specified && Col <= ColStart (with the interval negated).
